originalText.text: My kids have been seeing Dr Scantlebury since they were born and it’s been 9 years. I first met her at the HIP center when I oldest son was born and when she left was devastated. About a year after she left was pregnant again with my second son and I happened to run into her again. I have been with her since then. Both my kids and myself adore her. Her office is always clean and ready for patients and the wait time is almost no existent. I travel all the way from Brooklyn just to see her. She is so sweet and loving with your kids. I would definitely recommend her to everyone!! I give her 10 stars!!

originalText.text: My children have been seeing Dr. Scantlebury since they were born. She takes the time to address your concerns and answer your questions. She works in a timely fashion as well. The office is alway clean. She really is a fantastic doctor! My only negative is that reception can be a bit more organized. If you need paper work filled out for your child's camp you'd have to be on top of the office to get it done. Don't bother faxing; walk it in.

originalText.text: I wish that I could give Dr. Scantlebury 10 stars. She has been my son's pediatrician since he was 1 years old (he is now 16 years old) and she is EXCELLENT!  Both myself and my son adore her. Dr. Scantlebury treats her patients as though they are her own children. My son will continue with Dr. Scantlebury until he is passed the age of pediatrics and, if I am blessed to have more children, she will be their doctor as well. You really couldn't ask for a better doctor for your children :-)

originalText.text: Where do I begin?.. 12 years ago, I was referred to Dr. Scantlebury by the NICU after my son was born premature.  I was so nervous about meeting a new pediatrician for my son... I felt like I had 100+ questions to ask.  The moment I walked in with my boy, she automatically made me feel comfortable and I knew right away "we" were in good hands. She now sees both my boys.  I highly recommend Dr. Scantlebury!
